so.. I've been back from UP (HAHAH!) north for almost a week and haven't updated. but anyway, Isle Royal was awesome. Even though it was cold and overcast  for most of the time I was there, it was still one of the most beautiful places that I've ever been to.  and I never use that word. It was a great time, despite the blistering and slight departure of three of my toenails from their respective toes. and the not showering for 6.5 days. 

anyway, I think I will most definitely be going back next year, probably with my father, because I found out that he wanted to go. 

so, as soon as i get a day off (Monday or Wednesday) I will post the pictures. I printed them out today at work, and it ended up being 173!!! that's over $20! crazy!

I am kind of very excited. 

I am going to see Jackson Browne in July. it will be awesome.

I worked at Sue's new store today and it was the slowest thing ever. I was the only one there and I still just stood there for a large piece of time. but they have Arnold Palmer AriZona tea, so it was alright. the breakroom had a weird bench like the ones that used to be at Zap Zone. and there was no closet behind the counter for me to fart in.
whoooo!!! I'm done with school forever!!

So Chicago was mostly fun. I didn't get any of my paper of studying done that I was supposed to do during the 12 hours of transit time over the weekend, but that's ok. I'm glad I went - RENT was so much better with both Adam Pascal and Anthony Rapp than with Anthony Rapp and the Adam Pascal replacement Roger. I was happy that he got better and was able to do the show. Ugh, God. It was so good! They were crying! it was so emotional! I'm not ashamed to admit that I might have been crying at certain parts! hah! but i like chicago. i went to the field museum and that was awesome. the dinosaurs were a delight. i was kind of mad that the Aztec exhibit was sold out, though. 

but blugh, we ate so much food. bad for us food that I shat 5 times in 3 hours before leaving the hotel, then like... 3 more times that day. a $96 takeout bill for 4 people is just wrong. 

anywhoo... I just got back from the "electrician" cardiologist that works in the same office as the "plumber" that I saw before. He said there was nothing really wrong with me, but gave me the choice to go on Beta Blockers or not. I chose not, because I don't really want to be on lots of medications for everything. The less the better. He also told me that a low salt diet wouldnt be good for me, and that I need a higher blood volume so I should not cut back like the other doctor told me. 

anyway, i have to finish my paper (about synesthesia, so awesome!!) and study so hard for my exams tomorrow. Asshole made them all the same day.

ssooo... I think I'm going to do this Isle Royale thing. It should be fun, although it will be a lot of walking and carrying things, and no showers for a week. but I don't care about that, as long as I don't have my period! ahha! anyway, so i think i will have to start getting into shape now, so that I won't be one of those people who dies in the wilderness..... or has to be airlifted to Wisconson via seaplane. The only thing that I am worried about is my very active colon and its trecherous nature.  and the six hour boat rise to the island from Houghton.
Billy Mays and that other guy... I don't remember his name..... but they are going to have a new show on the Discovery channel called "Pitchmen."  I think that will be awesome.

God I hate Sarah Palin. She is such an ignorant and evil bitch. 

Why the fuck does she think she has a right to kill every non-human thing that moves? No one better kill a human fetus, because that would be wrong -- lets all just go out and throw some poison gas at wolf babies instead.  That will make everything better. And while we're at it, why don't we shoot thier moms, too. Then let's say we're doing it to feed our families. 

I think someone should follow her around in a goddamn helicopter until she can't run anymore then shoot her and leave her to die a slow and agonizing death. See how she likes it. 

I'm sure she'd take it like a maverick.

My parents got the house that they have been hoping to get. 

We will be living in Howell before July. 

I can't say that I'm entirely excited about leaving this house and everythin here, but I will try to make the best of it, since I really have no other options. 

I don't want to live in the ass-fucking crack of nowhere!

anyway, i has to get to bed, I have been watching too much Roswell and am very tired.

Damn you, HULU!! i checked the site for Roswell, because i was interested in taking a stroll down middle school memory lane and watch my favorite show from that time. so... i just watched 22 episodes since tuesday night after neurobio lab (where i skinned a cat, btw... gross). My mother says i'm obsessed, but i think that a lie. wither way i have to stop watching because only the first season is posted. i may have to just buy the damn series. i think i would have to call it my second or third favorite of all time, after the x-files and david the gnome. oh! and forever knight.  ugh, these dicks. they should post it this week so i can waste my last spring break watching it.

anywhoo.. i had my stress test, echocardiogram and i got my event monitor today. the tests went fine, altough my pulse and blood pressure were super high, but the lady told me that was normal because it was my first time (like the cold clammy hands of a nervous virgin!). but i must say that this damn event monitor is really annoying. i have to call this 1-800 number when it records stuff and transmit it like some walking dial-up modem. it happened twice in the first two hours of having it, and i have to wait on hold for a total of 20 minutes already. and it beeps real annoying like, which is gonna be awesome in class. 

also, my cousins are staying with us for a week or two, and thier dog is so fat and cute, but he barks at everything, this really loud, long and deep yet high pitched howl, especially in the middle of the night. he keeps waking me up. i really have to pee, but i dont want him to start screaming and wake everybody up. i think i might risk it, because i like my bed dry.

I think my phone got sick of me telling it that i hated it everyday and that it is the worst phone i've ever had, because it ran away again and I cant find it anywhere. so if anyone texts or calls me, i will not answers.

hahahahah! after that angryness, I listened to America's version of Muskrat Love and now I feel better. it's a really cool song, and it's even better because my mom once told me that it's her and myfather's song. that made me giggle.

I would like to take this time to once again profess my hatred for Uof M-Dearborn. Not only do they have no internship office for anthropology students/a reallly tiny department with only about... 5 faculty members, including the advisor, they have once again inticed my wrath with their inability to create class schedules of any value. with such a small campus, faculty can only teach certain classes once a year, and many of the upper-level classes are scheduled at the same time. here is a list of why i hate UM-D:

# 1: I was all happy that I could take a Population Genetics and Evolution  class, and that they were also offering a Comparative Anatomy of Vertebrates class, right when I discovered that what I really want to do is get a degrees in Biology and Anthropology. Beause I have no time to get a degree in bio, I decided to just get a minor. So I was all... yay!! then I discoveredthat they are overlap by a paltry 20 minutes! and it was a lab section, so i was like... maybe the professor will lat me sign up for both and just let me leave early from lab. no. so then I scheduled all this shit out, and was ready to register (which I have to do on my own, because there is no set of required courses forthe anthro department, and i dont have an assigned counsellor anyway, so i always have to explain things to new people). so i started to register and it was all.... !!!!!! PREQ ERROR !!!!!! and I was like... ok...  so i looked at the list of requirement and was all... no, you ass. but then i realized that no, i didnt take that calculus class last year, because i said "what will i ever need this for?" 

# 2: so then i was all.. damn.. i can take that class. because that was the one that i really wanted to take. but then i was happy, because i could then take the Comparative Anatomy class and the neurobiology class that i now found discovered that I could take. so i was all... yay! then I disovered that, since I only have one more class to take to finsh my art history minor, i looked for a class that I could take. but... oh yeah, no.. they all overlap with my two lab periods. the four upperlevel art history classes that are being offered this semester (the last until next fall), share two times, two during my tue/thur lab and two during my mon/wed labs. so now i have to decide if i want to finish my art history minor (which, hell yeah I am) or get a bio minor.

# 3: I have no idea how/where to go to get an internship, or if i will even be able to get one. there is only an intrnship office for history, CIS, sciences, poliical science, etc..... pretty much everything but anthropology. I think i will have to try the co-op office, ad see what i can get there. that's another thing that I hate. everywhere else requires internships to gradute, but not the awesome UM-D. I could go my entire school caree and not get any sort of internship or fieldschool. so basically, I would have absolutely no chance of getting hired in the job market. 

anyway, i could go one, but i am getting more and more pissed as i write. Plus, I've spent the past almost 4 hours trying to schedule my classes, and I have a paper due tomorrow that I have to write still. so goodnight.

Yeah, that's right... he was coming for your Speedos.

In other news, for one of my other Anthro classes - the one that I am fellowshipping for - our groups' community partner Kay Cumbow from the Citizens for Alternatives to Chemical Contamination has provided us with some very interesting information about nuclear power and the Fermi plant (which is the topic of my second group project). This class had made me think about persuing environmental anthropology instead of the other sorts of anthropology, and perhaps journalism or something of that sort. I hate to admit it, because he is kind of an arrogant ass, but the professor who teaches this class, and a few others that I have taken has a right to be. he is extremely radical and has had over 40 jobs in his lifetime -- which equals alot of experience. which is kind of admirable, if scary. plus, i would have to extend my schooling for at least another..... 2 semesters. which is ass.
